(fifthQuint)Comparing NAAT Testing to Standard Methods for the Diagnosis of Vaginitis.

 Several commercial nucleic acid amplification tests (NAAT) are available to identify causative organisms.

 One of these commercial tests has undergone validation published in a scientific journal, only in an STD clinic population.

 The primary outcome of this study is to compare NAAT diagnostic methods to traditional gold-standard tests for BV, VVC and TV in symptomatic and asymptomatic women in the general gynecology office as well as in a vulvovaginitis referral office.

 Addressing incorrect evaluation and diagnosis will lead to correct treatment for women suffering from vaginitis.

